{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper, 2 baking trays, silicone bread mat, rolling pin, round cookie cutter (6 cm), tongs, sealable container, oven","id":"r90092","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-wXBgxk04zho\/XZWqbEsbwnI\/AAAAAAAAfXs\/2fsehKrCPmAbWI_rJfpDf6EehuCg3L5RACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LIoXY-a-dbMUIfOY.png","title":"Kourabiedes (Greek moon biscuits)","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"250 g unsalted butter, softened"},{"content":"30 g raw sugar"},{"content":"1 egg"},{"content":"40 g brandy"},{"content":"450 g self-raising flour"},{"content":"120 g slivered almonds"},{"content":"250 g icing sugar"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"1.5 g","fat":"5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"11 g","calories":"397 kJ \/ 94 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place butter, raw sugar and egg into mixing bowl and blend <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>, or until mixture is fluffy and well combined."},{"content":"Add brandy and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Add flour and knead <b>2 min\/<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then knead for a further <b>1 min\/<b>, until pastry comes together and forms a ball. The pastry will be slightly sticky (see Tips). Transfer dough onto a floured silicone bread mat or work surface and flatten slightly."},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh almonds into it. Sprinkle almonds over dough and knead lightly with your hands to incorporate."},{"content":"Roll out dough between two sheets of baking paper into a rectangle (1 cm thick). Position a round cookie cutter (6 cm), over the bottom left edge of the rectangle so that you cut out a half circle."},{"content":"Re-position the cookie cutter over the top of the half circle so that a crescent moon shape is created by the pastry inside. Cut out the crescent moon and transfer biscuit onto prepared baking trays. Working in straight rows, repeat process with remaining pastry to form approx. 56 biscuits, re-positioning the cookie cutter so that crescent shapes are created everytime."},{"content":"Bake for 10-14 minutes (180°C), until golden brown."},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh icing sugar into it. While biscuits are still hot, use a pair of tongs to dip biscuits into the icing sugar until they are well coated. Place coated biscuits back onto baking trays and leave to cool."},{"content":"Serve immediately or transfer into a sealable container to store until use."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If the dough is very wet in step 4, add 1 tablespoon of extra self-raising flour and knead for a further 30 sec\/."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h","56 pieces"]}